Project Brief:
To create a traffic light control system

The first part of this project is to create a pedestrian crosswalk:
  The traffic lights (for the cars) will stay normally green but when the pedestrian button is pressed it will start a series of events that will turn the lights to red for a brief period.
    Logic:
      1. Traffic lights will be green by default.
      2. When the pedestrian button is pushed it A) sends a signal to the Arduino and B) sets the crossing light
      3. When the Arduino gets the pedestrian signal it wil:
          i. Turn off the green, start an internal timer, turn on the amber light.
          ii. When the timer reaches 10 seconds, it will turn off the amber lights, turn on the red lights
          iii. When the timer reaches 30 seconds, it will turn off the red lights, it will turn the amber lights on flashing
          iv. When the timer reaches 40 seconds, it will turn off the flashing amber lights, turn on the green lights, reset the timer

The second part of this project is to add a road of lesser importance to the system:
  The traffic lights for the main road cars will stay normally green until A) a pedestrian presses the pedestrian button or B) A car comes to the traffic lights on the road of lesser importance or C) Both A and B occur
